                        Fiscal Budget 2011: A modest fiscal tightening
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Press release, Ministry of Finance, 05.10.2010]</p>
                <p>Several targeted policy measures helped mitigating the effects of the international financial crisis on the Norwegian economy. Following a decline in mainland output of 1.4 per cent in 2009, growth in the Mainland economy is now forecast at 1.7 per cent in 2010 and 3.1 per cent in 2011, the latter about half a percentage point above trend growth. Unemployment has been kept at low levels throughout the downturn and is forecast at 3½ per cent both in 2010 and 2011.</p>
                
